VA. RAMALINGA SASTRYKalabharathi witnessed a scintillating vocal rectal by K. Vageesh in the company of M.S.N. Murty on violin, VV Ramana Murty on mridangam and Mandapaka Ravi of Vizianagaram on kanjira.Vageesh who is Trichy AIR station director got off to a tunefully grand start with theTodi Varnamfollowed byPranamamyaham Sreeprananaadhamin theoudhava vakra shadhava ragam Ranjaniand concluded it with excitingswaram. His choice next was a composition of Purandaradasa in the pentatonic scaleSuddhadhanyasiwhich he adorned with evocativeneravuandswaram.  Rendering ofEvarani Nirnayinchirira(Devamruthavarshini of Thyagaraja) turned out to be a welcome feature as it was the onlykritiwith which the audience was familiar thus far. Then followed a composition of his own in the pentatonic scale Rasikaranjani having Suddha Rishabham in place of the sharp Ri in Mohana. Renderingragam, tanamandpallaviin Todi inKhandajathi Triputa talamreplete with scholarly and resplendent exercises ofgrahabhedaminaalapanaandgathibhedaminswarakalpananext, he sang his way into the hearts of all alike in the auditorium.M.S.N. Murty on violin and Ramanamurty on mridangam along with Ravi on kanjira proved to be his peers in all aspects of showcasing of talent and with their delightful concern for aesthetics while following and in their turns (aalapana neravuand swaram on violin and eruditethanion mridangam and kanjira with reposeful exercises ongathiandyathirespectively) contributed splendour.Bottom Template Starts
